---
title: Cheesy Marinara Turkey Patties with Zucchini, Tomato & Scallion Couscous
description: Sometimes you want a burger without the bun, and sometimes you want a meatball made with turkey instead of beef. That’s why our chefs came up with this extra-comforting dinner idea: Ground turkey patties with garlic, scallion, Italian seasonings, and mozzarella, topped with marinara and more mozz, then baked to browned, melty, juicy perfection. It’s all served alongside hearty scallion couscous with golden pan-fried zucchini and tomato. Trust us: You’ll gobble this one right up!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/cheesy-marinara-turkey-patties-9c0ee17f.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/cheesy-marinara-turkey-patties-63c6c67465d6a363b50e2853-4e9f93f9.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/cheesy-marinara-turkey-patties-63c6c67465d6a363b50e2853
course: main course
time required: 30 minutes
cuisine: Italian
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
nutrition:
  calories: 650 kcal
  fat: 30 g
  saturated fat: 8 g
  carbohydrates: 56 g
  sugar: 9 g
  protein: 42 g
  fiber: 4 g
  sodium: 850 mg
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Peel and mince or grate @garlic{1%clove}. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens; finely chop whites. Trim and quarter @zucchini{1} lengthwise; slice crosswise into ½-inch-thick pieces. Dice @tomato{1} into ½-inch pieces.

In a #large bowl{}, combine @ground turkey{10%ounce}, garlic, scallion whites, @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}, half the @mozzarella cheese{1/2%cup}, half the @chicken stock concentrate{2}, @italian seasoning{2%tsp}, a big pinch of @salt{pinch}, and @pepper{}. Mix gently until thoroughly combined.

Form turkey mixture into 6 1 1/2-inch meatballs (12 meatballs for 4).

> Ground Turkey is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.

  > TIP: Rub your hands with a little oil first to prevent sticking.

Place meatballs on a lightly oiled #baking sheet{}; press down with your hand to form ½-inch-thick patties. Spoon @marinara{2.5%ounce cup} evenly over each patty and top with remaining mozzarella.

Bake on top rack until cheese is melted and patties are cooked through, ~{12-14%minutes}.

Meanwhile, in a #small pot{}, combine @israeli couscous{2.5%ounce}, remaining stock concentrates, remaining @italian seasoning{1%tsp}, ¾ cup water (1 1/2 cups for 4 servings), and a pinch of salt. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low; cook until tender, ~{6-8%minutes}.

While couscous cooks, heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add zucchini, salt, and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, until zucchini is browned and tender, ~{5-7%minutes}. In the last minute of cooking, stir in tomato until warmed through.

Fluff couscous with a #fork{}; transfer to pan with veggies. Add half the scallion greens and a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp}. Stir to combine. Taste and season with salt and pepper.

Divide couscous and turkey patties between plates. Garnish patties with remaining scallion greens and serve.